<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
The report of this species is a new distribution record to Wuyi Mountains. We think this species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. vietnamica" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="vietnamica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. vietnamica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
west group as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I." journalOrPublisher="Scopolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" pagination="1 - 122" refId="B7867379" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P., Shimizu, T., 2008. Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia 64: 1 - 122" title="Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae)" volume="64" year="2008">Sivec et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Head dark brown, slightly wider than pronotum; compound eyes dark; antennae and mouth-parts brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F8002472" captionText="Figure 4. Rhopalopsole fengyangshanensis Yang, Shi &amp; Li, 2009. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711848" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">4</figureCitation>
A). Tergum 9 possesses a small field on its hind margin. Tergum 10 possesses a central plate and two sclerotized bands on each side of the plate. Lateral projections of tergum 10 typically ending in a forked process, inner side has a finger-like ornamentation. Epiproct thick, hook-like, in top view, very blunt (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F8002472" captionText="Figure 4. Rhopalopsole fengyangshanensis Yang, Shi &amp; Li, 2009. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711848" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">4</figureCitation>
B and C).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
